Create a Kaggle Account: If you don't have one, sign up at Kaggle.

Obtain Kaggle API Credentials:
Navigate to your Kaggle account settings.
Scroll to the "API" section and click "Create New API Token".
This will download a kaggle.json file containing your API credentials.

Set Up Kaggle API on Your System:
Place the kaggle.json file in the appropriate directory:
Linux/Mac: ~/.kaggle/
Windows: C:\Users\<YourUsername>\.kaggle\

Ensure the directory has the correct permissions:
Linux/Mac: chmod 600 ~/.kaggle/kaggle.json

Install Kaggle Python Package:
If not already installed, run:
pip install kaggle

Download the Dataset:
Open a terminal or command prompt.
Navigate to your project directory:
cd /path/to/Brain_Tumor_Detection_System/dataset/

Use the Kaggle API to download the dataset:
kaggle datasets download -d masoudnickparvar/brain-tumor-mri-dataset

Extract the downloaded ZIP file:
unzip brain-tumor-mri-dataset.zip
Note: Ensure you have sufficient storage space, as datasets can be large.
